.geeksforgeeks.org/dsa/perfect-number/#naive-approach-divisor-sum-method">[=
Naive Approach] Divisor Sum Method - O(n) Time and O(1) Space</a></li><li><=
a href=3D"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/dsa/perfect-number/#expected-approa=
ch-optimized-divisor-search-method">[Expected Approach] Optimized Divisor S=
earch Method - O(sqrt n) Time and O(1) Space</a></li></ul></div><h3 id=3D"n=
aive-approach-divisor-sum-method" style=3D"text-align:left"><span>[Naive Ap=
proach] Divisor Sum Method - O(n) Time</span><b><strong> </strong></b><span=
>and O(1)</span><b><strong> </strong></b><span>Space</span></h3><blockquote=
><p dir=3D"ltr"><span>A simple Solution</span><b><strong> </strong></b><spa=
n>is to go through every number from 1 to n-1 and check if it is a divisor.=
 Maintain sum of all divisors. If sum becomes equal to n, then return true,=
 else return false.</span></p></blockquote><gfg-tabs data-run-ide=3D"true" =
